<div class="main2">
<h2 class="grey">Like this site? Get the book!</h2>

<p><img src="http://cdn4.explainthatstuff.com/atoms-under-floorboards-tiny.jpg" alt="Atoms Under the Floorboards book cover." height=150 class="ileftno" width=93></P>
<!--<p><img src="http://cdn4.explainthatstuff.com/atomsunder-tiny.jpg" alt="Atoms Under the Floorboards book cover." height=150 class="irightno" width=93></P>-->
<P>
Why do skyscrapers wobble in the wind? Why can't you cool your home with a giant block of ice? Could you microwave your dinner with a cellphone? What's the hidden connection between a bicycle and a suspension bridge? If questions like this are constantly buzzing round your brain, you'll love my new book, <I>Atoms Under the Floorboards: The Surprising Science Hidden in Your Home</I>, published worldwide by Bloomsbury. Please <a href="mybooks.php">click here</A> to find out more.</P>

